There's another problem.

in org.eclipse.hyades.trace.ui.internal.reports.XMLTraceReportWizard.generateClassStatistics


Consider the following code:

if(iterator.hasNext())
{
    buffer.append(" classObjects=\"");				
    while(iterator.hasNext())
	{
	buffer.append(((TRCObject)iterator.next()).getId()).append(" ");
	}
	buffer.append("\">");		
}


The buffer.append("\">"); line will not be called if(iterator.hasNext()) return false.

This line should be outside the if statement.

The fix is still not correct.  A space needs to be added before 'classClass' as shown below otherwise the classClass string will be appended to the previous line which causes an invalid xml file.

if (proc.getClassClass() != null)
